  "name": "Morrison COU2 — VAD hemolysis credibility assessment (Minimal profile, W-SI-01)",
  "description": "V&V 40 credibility assessment for CFD hemolysis prediction of the FDA generic centrifugal blood pump under ventricular assist device (VAD) conditions. COU2 evaluates whether the computational model can predict absolute hemolysis levels for a Class III VAD device at Model Risk Level 5. This package is filed under the Minimal profile and carries a sha256 hash but no digital signature, leaving structural integrity unverifiable (W-SI-01). All 13 credibility factors are assessed; seven achieved levels fall below required levels and six are flagged as epistemic gaps at MRL 5. Despite these gaps the decision record reflects Accepted for test-harness purposes.",
